pageContext.claim: “The Democrats have had this letter for three months. They could have brought it up at the hearing during, you know, in course during the hearing. Dianne Feinstein knew all about it and if she knew about it that meant [Charles] Schumer knew about it. And every Democrat knew about it.”
pageContext.analysis: Feinstein's Democratic colleagues were actually upset that she kept the letter accusing Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh of sexual misconduct under wraps as long as she did. In late July, the California Democrat received the letter from Rep. Anna G. Eshoo (D-Calif.). She did not inform colleagues until mid-September, about six weeks later.
